    {
      "q": "How much federal contract money goes to Florida?",
      "a": "Florida received $18.5B in federal contract obligations in FY2026 to date. Total FY2026-to-date obligations are $18.5B across 127,871 awards with an average award size of $145K; obligations fell 43.1% year over year. By fiscal year, obligations moved from $25.7B in FY21 to $32.5B in FY25 before declining to $18.5B in FY26."
    },
    {
      "q": "Which agencies award the most contracts in Florida?",
      "a": "The Department of Defense awards the most contracts in Florida, with $12.1B in FY2026-to-date obligations. Other major buying agencies in FY2026 to date include the Department of Veterans Affairs at $2.5B and the General Services Administration at $1.4B."
